
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "RandomKittens";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_GeneralTemplate.cshtml";
}
<head>
    <title>Random Kittens</title>
    <style>
        .carousel-inner img {
            max-width: 1000px;
            height: 300px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<h2>Random Kittens</h2>

<div>
    This is a series that I created as a test bench for various drawing techniques. The more recent works here represent new drawing techniques and ideas that I have implemented.
    As I continue to learn how to draw, expect to see more random kitten drawings here.
</div>

<br />

<div class="container mt-3" style="max-width: 500px; height: 500px">
    <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">

        <!-- The slideshow -->
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <h3>Random Kitten 1</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_1.jpg" />
                <p>First drawing in the random kitten series</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 2</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_2.jpg" />
                <p>Experiment with sitting posture and a scene drawn with a primitive art style</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 3</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_3.jpg" />
                <p>Experiment with laying down and early texture development</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 4</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_4.jpg" />
                <p>First drawing with the XP-PEN Star G640s Drawing Tablet. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 5</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_5.jpg" />
                <p>Another experiment involving the character laying down but with an introduction to shading and shadows. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 6</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_6.jpg" />
                <p>Summer scene with additional posture, shading, and texture experiments</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 7</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_7.jpg" />
                <p>New sitting experiment with shading involved</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kittens 1</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_8.jpg" />
                <p>Special-case drawing with two kittens featured instead of one</p>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <h3>Random Kitten 2</h3>
                <img src="~/images/Random Kittens/random_kitten_9.jpg" />
                <p>Special-case drawing with two kittens and one extra character featured. </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Left and right controls-->
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon"></span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon"></span>
        </a>

    </div>

</div>
